   {:e #blake3 "c53c6165356a9c1e6d2fa39ba05c43e62f68ea59fa99ee221c3f80ce356a0f83" :a :task/description :v "CONTEXT: Every string braid emits is a steering vector on the LLM's activation manifold (STEERING_MANIFOLD.md). The observe subcommands must NAVIGATE the knowledge manifold, not LIST data. A flat list activates 'reading a report' mode. Structured output ending with a computed question activates 'investigating a lead' mode. The question IS the acquisition function rendered as natural language.\n\nKERNEL SIDE — ObservationSummary + all_observations(): Same as prior design. ObservationSummary struct with entity, title, body, confidence, category, concept_name, concept_entity, timestamp, tags, agent_name, link_count. Sorted by timestamp desc.\n\nKERNEL SIDE — observation_steering_question(): NEW. Computes a steering question from the observation graph. For list context: uses co_occurrence_matrix() to find the top bridge-gap pair (zero jaccard), returns 'What connects [concept-A] and [concept-B]?'. For search context: takes search results, returns 'N findings corroborated by M agents — consider [top convergent action]' or 'Top unresolved: [highest-confidence finding without task/resolution]'. For show context: takes an entity, finds the nearest observation in the same concept that it has no link to, returns 'Related but unlinked: [observation-title]. How does it connect?'. For recent context: identifies the dominant concept in recent observations and the least-observed concept, returns 'Recent focus: [dominant]. Gap: [least-observed]. Explore?'. Uses existing functions: frontier_recommendation(), co_occurrence_matrix(), concept_inventory(), find_nearest_observation(). Zero LLM calls. Pure computation.\n\nCLI SIDE — Four subcommands: (1) braid observe list [--concept FILTER] [--limit N]: Groups by concept cluster. Each group: concept display name (from C9-P6), member count, confidence range, top 3 observations by confidence. Ends with steering question from observation_steering_question(ListContext). (2) braid observe search PATTERN [--sort relevance|confidence|recent] [--limit N]: Substring match, ranked by 0.4*relevance + 0.3*link_count + 0.2*confidence + 0.1*recency. Shows matches with concept tag and confidence. Ends with steering question from observation_steering_question(SearchContext, results). (3) braid observe show ENTITY: Full body, confidence, category, concept, tags, timestamp, agent. Incoming links (what depends on this). Outgoing links (what this depends on). Ends with steering question from observation_steering_question(ShowContext, entity). (4) braid observe recent [N]: Most recent N (default 20) with concept tag and confidence. Ends with steering question from observation_steering_question(RecentContext, recent_entities).\n\nCLAP STRUCTURE: Convert braid observe to subcommand-based. 'braid observe TEXT' remains valid for creation. 'braid observe list|search|show|recent' are new subcommands.\n\nGOLD STANDARD OUTPUT (from STEERING_MANIFOLD.md Section 2): braid observe list should produce output like: [stagnation-verification] (12 obs, conf 0.85-0.95) followed by indented top observations, then [schema-c8-violations] (8 obs, conf 0.80-0.90), then -> What connects stagnation-verification and schema-c8-violations? (0 shared observations, 3 shared spec refs). braid observe show should produce: full body, links, then -> Related but unlinked: 'C9-AGENT-IDENTITY-GAP'. How does it connect to this finding?\n\nACCEPTANCE: (A) braid observe list groups by concept with steering question at end. (B) braid observe search AUDIT returns ranked results with steering question. (C) braid observe show displays graph context with steering question. (D) braid observe recent shows concept tags with steering question. (E) braid observe TEXT creation still works. (F) All 4 output modes. (G) Steering questions are computed from graph structure, not hardcoded. (H) On live store, steering questions reference actual concepts and bridge gaps. FILES: crates/braid-kernel/src/concept.rs (all_observations + observation_steering_question), crates/braid/src/commands/observe.rs, crates/braid/src/commands/mod.rs. EFFORT: 10h." :op :assert}
